into its top. The fact that it has no apparent doors or windows helps, too...
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 420 ADJ1=312
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Broken glass has been set into the top of the wall, presumeably to keep out
anyone who might try to climb it. In several places the jagged pieces form
interesting combinations, as though the wall's builders wanted to mute its
ugliness with a little bit of beauty.
*DESCRIPTION_END
